{"questionId":"12218","questionHtml":"<p class=\"indent2\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;\">Find an expression for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"bc\">\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n</math></span> in terms of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{a^2} + bc = a\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>a</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\Rightarrow bc = a - {a^2}\">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>a</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</strong></em><em><strong>&nbsp; N1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12218","referenceCode":"EXM.2.AHL.TZ0.22a.ii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find an expression for b c in terms of a .","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.14—Introduction to matrices"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}